
Learning Outcomes

  - After completing this module, you will be able to:
  - Recall the history and development of insurance and the economic and social role of insurance. 
  - Distinguish between types of insurance policies and recognise key terms and concepts.
  - Identify the purpose and steps in claim handling process.
  - Describe the key components of effective communication skills and strategies.
  - Recognise types of insurance fraud and the indicators of fraudulent claims.
  - Discuss investigative techniques in fraud detection and prevention strategies.
  - Describe the procedures for calculating insurance payouts.
  - Outline types of policy limits and types of reinsurance. 
  - Discuss digital transformation in claims handling and future trends in insurance technology. 
